76561198089899444,Recommended,233860,34593814,Posted: 29 August,all,Osric,"This really is a great game. Its been developed by a single dev for most of its life although there is now a team on board to push it over the finish line. I returned this on my first purchase, put off by the clunky UI and the camera controls and the graphics are hardly breath-taking although it certainly has its own beauty. But this is a unique gem that rewards those who persevere. Watch Aviticus Dragon's youtube series if you want to see this game in all its glory, the game lends itself so well to a narrrative that he's almost made a mini-series out of it.  You have base building, squad management, crafting, exploration, rpg elements and so much more. Its perhaps best described as a  cross between Rimworld and Mount and Blade. It is perhaps the most ambitious one man project I've ever seen and whilst it feels held together with duct tape at times it will often surprise you with the depth of some of the systems running beneath the surface.There are a number of different starting options, but all of them fling you into the world with little more than a loin-cloth. Everyone, and I mean everyone will tear you a new one and you're reduced to sneaking around and scavenging in the hope of finding a stick with which to defend yourself and more than once you'll find yourself beaten to a pulp and left for dead at the side of the road. No-one will help you. But every time you survive a kicking you will get stronger. Maybe you'll come across a similarly unfortunate unconscious vagabond and steal his stuff just as you've been looted so many times before. Once you have a few sticks you'll sell them and buy some food. Little by little you'll build up your stats and you finances, commit a few burglaries and finally have enough cash to hire another puny character to level up and help you in building your empire. Maybe you'll build a farm and sell the produce, maybe a mine with a small shack. As your humble retinue finally gains a foothold, builds some defensive walls, starts researching new tech you'll have your revenge on the  bandits who used to abuse you. But be careful, take on too strong a foe and your unconscious squad members will be captured by passing slavers and and you'll have to try to sneak into their base, pick the locks on their cages and rescue them, or worse they'll be taken by fogmen and eaten alive.Little by little you'll establish outposts, multiple squads, make your fortune and stride across the landscape looting, pillaging, trading, manufacturing, exploring ruins, waging war and exacting revenge upon those who had once treated you with contempt. You'll form alliances or feud with factions, and fence your stolen loot with the Shinobi thieves. Your humble settlement will grow into a town with specialist farmers, weavers, miners, medics and engineers and guards manning the walls with crossbows. They'll resupply your weary war-party when they return from another adventure, half starved, carrying their wounded  comrades with an ancient manuscript for you researcher, and some high grade equipment, the reward for a hard won battle with mechanical spiders. They'll be fed, their wounds treated as they rest in your hospital building then load out for another foray to capture a bandit king for his bounty or ride to the rescue of one of your less formidable squads bleeding out in the wilderness.This is an unbelievable game and there's nothing quite like it. If you're the sort of person for who gameplay is all and you can see past some of the rough edges and the steep learning curve, you can set your own goals and have a decent imagination, do yourself a favour and buy this game. Its due to have another large chunk of an already vast map released any day and its well on the way towards completion probably by next summer. I cannot recommend this game highly enough, its a masterpiece."
