76561198039532140,Recommended,233860,32478395,Posted: 16 June,all,UofMTigerFan,"Kenshi is something that you don't see very often. In a way, it can be called ""You are not special: the game.""Given a few starting options and an admittedly pretty hilarious character customization, where the face isn't what you work on, but instead deciding how buff or hunchback you want to be, you're thrust into an apocalyptic world where half the things want to kill you, even more if you're not human, a quarter wants to enslave you, and the last handful of people couldn't care less unless you've got some cash on you.Through the most rigorous training exercises of being beaten up by starving farmers and carrying rocks for days on end, I trained up Shortstoat the soldier to be a buff and mean man. Swords no longer hurt him and he can carry one thousand pounds and still run. Yet he's still nothing on his own.You need to put time and effort into learning this game, but the payoff will be very worth it. You can create anything you want, you could be an adventurer, you could create a city, or you can make an empire. Drug smuggling, sword fighting, farming, mining, all different professions you can do if you're willing to do the grind."
