,Recommended,233860,31097884,Posted: 12 April,all,Max Pafco,"DISCLAIMER: I am fairly critical of games and originally had a negative view on this one; I have changed my view after thorough review. The negatives of this game can simply be summed up to technical (early access) issues and the fact that this game type will certainly not appeal to some gamers.I purchased this game awhile back and, upon starting it up, felt as if I had opened a chunky book on advanced quantum theory and Karl Marx's volumes of his work ""Capital"", and proceeded to read them at the same time. This work of art is an unforgiving delight and I regret none of the hours developing my faction, ""Max's Legion"".In a nutshell, you will accumulate squad members (if you want), level them up, build a base, start fighting bandits, move up to swamp ninjas, maybe venture to cannibal territory, and ultimately cash in the exorbitant bounty on the Bugmaster and his army of Starship Trooperesque spiders. That's just one way to play, as you could easily just buy the game's equivalent to an ox and shuffle trade goods back and forth as a merchant, and so on. Of course, the game has limitations like substantive dialogue and ""missions"" being relatively absent, which are constantly being added.So, if the have the time and funds, I would recommend this game; this is especially true as the game is polished into an even shinier diamond over time. Enjoy."
