,Recommended,233860,33175356,Posted: 3 July,all,Benishe323,"My favorite game of all time with the most time I've put into a game other than world of warcraft pre-BC. It is a game littered with amazing RPG mechanics and decent enough customization so that you can tap into your imagination and create whatever faction you want from scratch, strengthen your characters as they go from being bottom feeders to battle hardened samurais or ninjas, and build pretty much anywhere on the map.This game has a lot to offer for anyone who enjoys RPG's, sandbox-type games, and there is plenty of city building/management to go around with larger and stronger factions obviously needing more farmers to keep everyone fed, a viable power source to keep the lights on, enough iron ore and rocks to make more buildings and tools, and decent marksmen mounting the crossbow turrets that often adorn a towns walls.On top of all that it is an incredibly well-priced game for the amount of play-time you get out of it. 20 bucks, a few dollars less during a sale, and you've got yourself an easy 60+ hour experience and that's only if you dedicate yourself to a single playthrough. You can delve into the mods which tickle your fancy, try unique New Game Starts to spicen things up, and even make your own mods for the game to either improve your personal experience or to export so the community benefits from your passion.So get Kenshi, you'll be happy you did."
