,Recommended,233860,21183948,"Posted: 13 February, 2016",all,Adenauer Forst,"An RPG game with quite a nice graphical detail and quality. Kenshi is quite fun and addictive even though it's still in Alpha stage. It has a few bugs here and there (mainly movement), but they are normally just a slight annoyance. If you know and love the web browser RPG games Caravaneer and Caravaneer 2, you will probably love Kenshi as well. It is similar in many ways, with the difference being that Kenshi doesn't have a story line and is in 3D.Build version when I wrote this review: v0.74.32.Some tips I'd like to share with everyone who is new to Kenshi:-- Ctrl + Shift + F11 will probably be your best friend in the game when it comes to getting characters unstuck.-- If you are having problems renting a bed to sleep for your character to recover quickly, and you have more than one character in your party, use any of them to pick up whoever that needs a rest and place them on the bed. This allows you to use the bed for free as well. Recovery while standing still is a very slow process unless your characters have a high toughness value.-- Even with the fast forward button, Kenshi can still be fairly slow. The start of Kenshi will probably be a slow one unless you get lucky. Don't worry about creating a settlement early on as it isn't really important. I took about 100 game days to start establishing my settlement after I got enough money and was satisfied with my crew members' skill level.-- The training dummies provided at towns can only train melee strength until level 4. Don't bother leaving your characters to train after that because you'll be wasting your time.-- Make use of the melee defence button for weak characters. You can train their melee defence easily this way while buying time for your attacking characters.-- Loot high value items from bandits only (weapons, headgear, shoes, and armour). Keep an eye out for sand ninjas because their armour is nice and light, and so is their weapons. Take note that their stats are quite high though."
76561198006148422,Recommended,233860,8238598,"Posted: 23 December, 2013",all,JonnyD73,"I have been playing this game almost from the time it was GreenLit.  It is an amazing mix of RPG, RTS, City Management. Even without all the planned features implemented yet. It is still worth playing. When this game is complete, it will be one of the most awsome games to date. The developement is amazing, considering the size of the dev team and that they probably do most of the coding during their free time, they get quite a bit done.  There are bugs, but the team is responsive to bug reports. In the end I can't stress enough, that this game is one that will provide hours and hours of game play and provide the player with the most choices in how to play. Be a lone wanderer just making his way by his sword. Lead a group of mercenaries to fame and riches. Become the most notorious bandit in the known lands, Found a city and produce goods for trade. I give this game a 9 out of 10 for being original and having an amazing dev team. I hope after this project is done, the dev team continues to produce more amazing titles.Update:For those that like the pros and cons listed.Pros:1. Freedom - Explore, develope, wander, or waste your time as you please.2. Character Developement - You gain skill when you use it. Not if you have exp to spend on it.3. Aspect View - You can watch over from above or get into an almost 3rd person view of your party.4. Sandbox - You can build a base, or even a city.5. Weapons - Lots of weapons to fit your fighting styles.6. Random - Bandit and Canibal raids. If you have a city or base, Bandits and Canibals will find you.7. Unique - RTS meets RPG with City Management and Crafting.Cons:1. Goals - With no ultimate goal, you can get to a point where you have to say, what do I do next. If there were a rival system. Or just a set of acheivements to get, it would add much more flavor IMO.2. Ranged Combat - I have seen in the blogs that this is comming, but until it does, there is a chunk missing from the combat tactics.In the end, I am hoping for a bit of polish to make this game great.  The next Update is supposed to be out soon and I can't wait.  Even with all the little frustrations and bugs.  I have had many hours of fun with this game and it has already been more than worth the $20 I paid for it.Update:Ok, so with the customization, I have had some of the most random fun you could have. With the ability to customize your character and your followers as you find them and all the new races. I made a human character that kept hiring people of various races and then when setting up their appearance (it allows you to change their appearance and even their name after you agree to pay to take them on) to be as small as possible. You end up with tiny goblin looking creatures. They have the same stats and abilities, they just look strange. It is funny to watch your little group of angry goblin people with big plank weapons chase down an opponent and beat him to death for trying to attack your base. I will say again, the game is worth the price just for that experience alone."
