76561198006276140,Recommended,233860,9200214,"Posted: 20 February, 2014",all,[killjoy],"EARLY ACCESS IMPRESSIONSIf and when this game reaches completion, I will update this review as necessary.That being said, for an Early Access game, I would still recommend this to anyone looking for a fun free-roaming open-world RPG. There are various starting scenarios, though ultimately you play a character (or characters) stranded in the middle of nowhere; the overall objective - to be or not to be completed at your leisure - is to recruit other survivors and literally build a community from the ground up that you can all survive the many dangers of the harsh wasteland within. One of the main draws is being able to control upwards of 20+ characters (believe this number will eventually be much, much larger) who are capable of doing various jobs: farmers, scientists, labourers, bounty hunters, warriors, bodyguards, thieves, assassins, engineers, merchants, traders and more; the neat thing here is that all you need to do to train a skill up is to use it, which allows any given character to potentially do anything and everything you'd like them to.Graphics aren't much at the moment, but this game will likely never have a huge emphasis on visuals since you will spend most of the time zoomed out far enough out to not care. The sound is coming along nicely, so far, though it definitely needs more work. AI isn't fully implemented yet and is a bit single-minded, but the 'to-do' list in this area is sounding really promising at this point. Still. The game has a certain addictive quality to it."
