76561198104089191,Recommended,233860,12016019,"Posted: 7 September, 2014",all,Bushi Neko,"Waaaaay back in 2014 I acquired this little game. Kenshi. The Massive Desert Walking / Dying game. It really had next to zero to do in it then. It grew, changed, grew... and I got bored. Very bored. Like so bored I shelfed it for only the occasional look in on the updates.Today, I loaded it up again. Wow. Its an amazing new game compared to the first days of EA. It is a true Free to Do What You Want game.  Start as a loser. Start as a nobody leaning toward loser. Start as a retired office now a loser. The bottom line is, you start as a nobody. Some starts by your choice are harder, some easier. Play is hard at first. No hand holding, no leveling up. Most everyone and thing you meet at first will hand you your backside if you bring a fight to it. Each thing you do increases your skill in that thing, not some overall level up as most of us are used to. You also can have a squad of followers. Once you have more than one character on your team, you can swap between them, or play as only one as your primary ( what I tend to do still. ) If one dies, you can stay and keep the game going as any character on your team.  You can also build settlements, and drop even more peeps in there. Have workers, prisoners, slaves or simply be a raging bandit and take what you want... and ransom those you take in battle ( not all NPC can be ransomed ) Be a bounty hunter.. etc etc.. its your game. Nobody makes you do anything.Want to be a thief? Go for it. Just be ready to spend time in jail.Murdering thief? Go for it.You can get enslaved, and that sux, but you can try and run for freedom.You can be captured by cannibals. Good luck there. But you can get away. Maybe.Want to be a pure Merchant only letting gaurds fight for you? Go for it.You get the idea.Female / Male characters. Customize from head to toe, WITH a Workshop of some extra things.Weapons, and workshop there also.This is a bit of a slow mover, so dont jump in expecting to roam the land as a mighty warlord, it takes time. But it's really where it was saying it was going."
