,Recommended,233860,34905143,Posted: 12 September,all,[SG] Octa,"Normally, I don't really get on to the Early Access hype, and try to stay away from them in general. I've learned the hard way that buying a game before it's done can be a really bad experience.  However, Kenshi is definitly an exception to that rule.Taking up Kenshi can be a grueling task. The game is brutal, but not totally unfair. It's difficult to get off your feet, but not impossible. The basebuilding aspect of the game is what drew me in, and it's what keeps bringing me back every few months.The team behind the game releases new patches fairly consistantly, and they only break the game completely like one out of every ten, so that's good.The world is interesting, honestly I love the game's design and world building. The graphics could be considered dated, but this is an indie game. I guess graphics aren't my #1 concern, considering I play games like Dwarf Fortress and Rimworld.In short, I would consider a $20 price tag for this game well worth it, even if it isn't done yet. The biggest issues with the game are when it just refuses to work (which sadly happens every once in awhile with new patches). But the game itself if fun enough to keep me coming back to it even after owning it for so long now.7-8/10, would recommend to anyone who likes base builders, world exporation and survival games"
