,Recommended,233860,35135738,Posted: 22 September,all,EmperorHeartles,"Kenshi is very much a niche game. Not everyone is going to enjoy it and yes it can be a little too sandboxy at times. The long development time also made me question whether or not I would enjoy this game when I first bought it during a sale. However, I must say that I have enjoyed it a lot.What I enjoy:- Constant updates and support: In the year or so that I have owned Kenshi, the game has improved quite a bit and runs a lot smoother on my Laptop than before.- Modding Tools: Using the FCS takes time to learn but when you get the hang of it, you can do a lot more such as new factions, weapons, etc.- Beak Things: Those little pieces of... hate fighting them. I feel like I accomplish something when my squad kills one.What I don't enjoy:- Crashing and Bugs: It's Early Access still. Bugs and crashing are to be expected. I'm not going to like it when it happens, but the game has been getting smoother over time with updates.- FPS: The game can be very cpu intensive. Not graphic card intense, cpu. Because of all the wandering groups and npcs going about their day, following their ai. Sometimes the FPS can slow to a crawl.- Limited Modding Information: I assume the reason for the lack of information out there is because the game changes over time, sometimes breaking mods and changing code. Still, there is a very sporadic and basic amount of information on modding out there (at least reading wise. Not sure about YouTube videos, I know they exist but I'm more of a reader than a listener.)Overall: Kenshi is a great game that suits MY preferences. I enjoy it a lot and will continue to play, neglecting my other responsibilities like work (actually, I'm late for work right now. Oops.) and school. YOU may not. I can't gurantee that you'll love Kenshi but what I can say is to give it a chance.This isn't about being a hero that can slaughter everything in its path. It is a story of survival, accomplishment, and being eaten by Beak Things."
