,Recommended,233860,35499967,Posted: 5 October,all,ZarkXavox,"Kenshi offers what no other game can do for me, and I'd have to say that this game easily ranks in some of the best games I've ever played. The replaybility of Kenshi is godlike - I've played it like a normal RPG, like an RTS, and like a city-builder all in the same campaign.One of my favorite things about Kenshi is that you can adjust it to how you want! Do you think it requires too many cactuses to make a meal? Do you want darker and longer nights? You can open up the modding tools to create a fix in just a couple clicks with little modding experience. You can even edit/create towns, AI, factions, and tinker around to make it a world you want. If that isn't your thing, you can visit the workshop for a great list of mods to get.Lastly, it does have bugs here and there, but I haven't had any game breaking issues after 110 hours of gameplay. You can import your save into a new game/world if something acts up, and it's a great way to refresh the population if you change any settings/add custom towns."
