76561198041349827,Recommended,233860,23329814,"Posted: 1 June, 2016",all,Red,"While early access and open world sandbox are two words which usually bring forth any reaction from \""this has potential\"" to \""i would rather cut off my arm with a rusty spoon than play this game for another minute\"" but personally i think it\'s on the good end of the spectrum.Firstly, the game is as previously stated, an open world sandbox, but with a nice twist, as opposed to the usual solitary experience were you craft, build and improve all by yourself, this game encourages you to recruit other npcs to be controlled by you. And by \""encourage\"" i mean it in the same way disease encourages you to go see a doctor, while not always necessary, it\'s still the best course of action, mostly because your new \""hero\"" is as much of a hero as the crack addict that lives next door to meThe gameplay is quite nice, they call the fighting is squad based, meaning you will be fighting with a group, against a group, a big part of combat is also the standard gear and their bonuses, but they also have a skill system, were the skills become better the more your people use them, and some gear gives negative stat bonuses, which means that heavier armor is quite balanced.You can build too! You can start your own town (though i don\'t think you can get any \""normal\"" citizens) were you can craft several houses and a ton of machines that do stuff for example, you can make a blacksmith, weaver, chainmaking station etc. you can also farm within your town, which is done by building the respective farm building, for example a wheat farm, then employing one of your guys to work there, but before you can build any of those you need to research them, which you slowly do by making the highest level research bench you can and staffing a person there.A lot of people tell me to judge early access games by their current state, and not their potential, and while i somewhat agree, i don\'t even need to judge it by it\'s potential to tell you this game is great, even in it\'s current state.The main problem with the game is simple, a lot of bugs, but however it doesn\'t crash too frequently, except when you mess about in the settings too much, and sometimes buildings lose their textures and get a placeholder one, and sometimes the npcs get stuck not doing anything.But despite all that, i would recommend this game to anybody who likes open world sandboxes and a challenge, and don\'t care much for high-rez games and don\'t mind some bugs and crashes"
