,Recommended,233860,35162424,Posted: 23 September,all,JaredTriesGaming,"This review comes from a up-and-coming Curator for a multi-tagged gaming Steam group.To make this review simple to read, I'll explain the major pros and cons, with the pro/con titled in all capsUTTERLY UNQIUE CONCEPTThis game is like no other I've ever seen in my years of gaming and reviewing; The concept is simple, but never seen put into a game before; A hyper-realistic post-nuclear war[At the least, it has that feeling] setting in which, no matter what start you have, you'll always have a challenge, where no events is scripted and everything is entirely by chance.ULTRA-REALISMThis game IS extremely realisitic; The game won't hold your hand for new or struggling-players, but it is also fairly easy to adapt and learn. Events, such as bandit attacks, wild animals, robbery, merchant arrivals, and price changes, aren't scripted and are near-completely random. The game-changer to some of these, mainly wild animals and certain raids, will be where you [eventually] settle. For example, The Borderzone-Swamp[Which is where I currently stand] was a bad choice; While bandits are generally weak here, the nearby Swamp Raptors are a problem; They're stronger than my band of 5, and they eat the crops. However, after a couple of raids by them, I learned to keep my men in their houses until I could have a wall built up. For the smart player, there is always a solution to every problem in this game.PURE SANDBOXYou are never forced to go to one faction or another, or to be stuck with one job. In this game, no matter what start you choose, you can become anything you desire, so long as you can over the boundaries of your start. Nothing is scripted, everything is possible.-------BAD PERFORMANCEThis game, understandably due to it being in beta, has some bad performance. No matter your computer build, DO NOT EXPECT 60FPS. This game is just poorly optimized, and only the game designers will be able to fix it.CHALLENGINGThis game WILL NOT hold your hand whatsoever. You can make the game easier with some mods and settings, but no divine blessing or intervenetion from the game; You can, by sheer chance, be hit by ultra-geared mega bandits in your 2nd in-game day. This is a con for newer/casual players, but a pro for the more hardcore survivalists."
