,Not Recommended,233860,35108714,Posted: 21 September,all,Sargos,"This game wants to be ambitious but pretty much fails in what it actually delivers. It has a huge (mostly empty) map, combat and basic base building systems in place, and some RPG like statistics. Each system is there and sort of works at a basic level but none of them have any depth and everything is plagued with unpolished user interfaces and a feeling of being slapped together with duct tape.Keep in mind that this review is for the almost completed game. It's just a few months from 1.0 according to the official blog. There are some reviews on here from 2-3 years ago that no longer apply (but a lot of them have portions that you could copy and paste today and they would still be true).Game is best summed up as: ""Wide as an ocean but deep as a puddle"""
,Recommended,233860,1989458,"Posted: 26 April, 2013",all,SlyGoat,"This is one of the few early access titles I've not regretted picking up early. It delievers a decent level of content already with a lot more promised on the horizon, and it actually abides by the spirit of what early access is rather than just being a sort of super early preorder; the developer actually uses community feedback to determine what features to focus on.The game itself is also very engaging, but that's more a matter of personal preference. At its core it's primarily a sandbox game (and as far as I'm aware the first sandbox game to feature primarily desert, which strikes me as odd; think of the symbolism!), though at the moment it isn't as flexible as you'd expect a sandbox game to be. Even in early access, however, there is a decent level of easily accessible moddibility to be found. You can tweak and create weapons, NPCs, characters and even build NPC towns and modify the base mechanics of the game with a simple and relatively straightforward GUI.There is unfortunately not much more to say about the game at this stage because it is still early access and seemingly a long way off from release, which may be enough to put a lot of people off. Let me repeat because it can't be overstated: this game is made by an incredibly small team (it was a team of one for a long time) and it isn't likely to be finished in 2014, maybe not even in 2015. But it's already a fun game at its core if you like squad based RPGs or town building simulators or a mix of both, and it is steadily progressing. I also expect that over the coming year it'll start seeing some decent modding."
