76561198058911966,Recommended,233860,9091298,"Posted: 13 February, 2014",all,The Lizard King,"To begin, this game is a mess. However, it's in Alpha, and the producers are working very hard.Describing it is difficult - You start off with nothing but a sword and a pair of pants. Literally anyone can kill you at the beginning of the game - most of your first hours will be spent scavenging off of corpses or running for the safety of towns.Eventually, you can build your own town, and the nature of the game completely changes. It becomes a sort of Age of Empires mixed with the Sims. You'll need to keep recruiting people and assigning them jobs - you'll need miners, blacksmiths, warriors, medics, scientists. Eventually (and I mean VERY eventually) you can wage wars agains the other factions, destroy bandit camps, and become the ruler of the desert. If you've ever seen six-string samurai, you'll have an idea of the setting.The soundtrack is pretty amazing, especially given the homemade feel of this game overall.Despite all of the problems, this game is addictive, and so original that it's hard to stop thinking about it in your off-time. If you're one of those people who doesn't mind unfinished games, dying all the time, and frequent crashes, I'd recommend picking this up. Even considering the somewhat high price tag, you'll likely put enough time into it to make it worth it."
