76561198082123142,Recommended,233860,16482842,"Posted: 17 June, 2015",all,xico,"Kenshi has become my go-to game for sandbox aventure. The development of the game is going at the pace to be expected for such a small team. It is an ambtious project and I am confident they can pull it off.I started as a loner in the game, forced to run for my life from town to town. Now my tribes have settled the deserts across the map. Communities of individuals capable of labor and battle. With the introduction of a slaver faction, I have taken to roaming the lands for would-be captors. Narratives will be developed from each gamer's playthrough. My point being that a story-weaving gamer will likely take great enjoyment from this game in its current state.The game is about to undergo a major overhaul, with new biomes, an expansion of fauna varieties, and improved faction AI. At the time of this posting, there still remain pathing issues with gates and a host of bugs which are being addressed. Please keep in mind the subsequent pro/con list below is subject to adjustments as development continues.+ Great building system and tech tree that continues to expand+ Unit organization permits efficient distribution of tasks over many isolated towns and forts+ High interactivity with those around you+ Gameplay that encourages treating your community as your greatest resource+ Open styled gameplay, I have some characters that run shops in cities while others hunt slavers. Militarism is not essential to succeed.- Still in development, lacking much landscape and biological diversity-""                              "", pathing system can be annoying, along with numerous bugs-""                               "", as much as there are many achievements to seek in a new game, content becomes limited after 15-20 hoursThis is not a game for people who are looking for a finished product soon. Nor is it suitable for folk who want fast results and progress. This is a game of protracted events and would only keep the attention of gamers with such sensibilities. When I want a high-paced action experience I don't pick this up.This is a game for individuals who want to see the progress of a well-made game through its evolution, unlike some other early access titles. It's suitable for gamers who like to dabble with genres of RPG, town builders, and RTS. If you are on the fence about its development I would wait, but holy scat if you're looking for a great game to enjoy in its growth this is the best early access title I've supported!!"
