,Recommended,233860,18080631,"Posted: 17 September, 2015",all,AlaskanBeard,"I'll preface this review by saying a lot of the negative reviews do have merit. The dev is not super fast to push out updates, and the game is by no means near finished, but you have to keep in mind just how ambitious this game is. There are hundreds, maybe thousands of mechanics they're tyring to add and iron out before this game moves forward.I would also like to mention that I have somewhere closer to 300 hours on this game, rather than the 60 steam shows.This game is super ambitious and I don't think I've played anything quite like it. When I look for a sandbox RPG, this is what I want. There's a good progression and a ton of content to explore, even though the game is still in alpha. Building up your base and setting trading up, the combat, RPG elements, everything is just super well paced and fun, not to mention each playthrough is different. There are a lot of bugs, depending on the version you're playing, but most of them aren't game breaking, and the few that have been, there's enough content to just gloss over that piece of the game and do something else.More recently (closer to version .75) the dev has been working a lot on updating some of the mechanics and fixing a lot of the bugs. These last few versions have been the most polished and balanced between new features and bug fixes that have been released.All in all, it's definitely worth the $20 for the game. I've gotten tons of fun out of it and it's a blast to come back to every update. I've found myself playing more and more each time."
