y agreed to join our cause in agreement to living in our villiage. We had also stumbled across a man nearly starved to death in the desert canyons named Feck. He joined us as well.We made our way to  the Top of a Platue where we set up our outpost for the time being. We had not yet decided on a name, though we were happy about the location due to the long hike and it was hidden atop a platue above the desert cliffs. Only one way in, which made it easy to defend, or so we thought.After a week we had a stone mine up and running, we have now two houses and we have a farm with a wind generator. We thought things were going great, even had a well outside of the villiage a short ways. That was our mistake. A group of Sand Ninjas and Bandits had come into contact with each other, not far from our well. They Seveirly Injuried Weke and he managed to get back to the Villiage, however so did they.We managed to hold them off, mostly due to their in fighting, and Rin was quite skilled with her Katana. Luckily we only had 3 injuries, Weke, Gardener and Set were beridden for days. Now we look to the future, what is next? how can we further our villiage, are our walls enough? That is the story of Toukanai Villiage Thus far."""
