,Recommended,233860,20103672,"Posted: 29 December, 2015",all,José,"(Due to bad internet, I've got much less hours on record than I've actually played)I'm updating my review, which was made in 2014.I still recommend this game. Since my purchase of it, it has been updated, patched onto and received many additions. That, however, does not make it complete, or stable.What are you getting right now?The game is a survival sandbox-rpg where you command a squad of people with different skills and attributes, you can build in a vast, albeit a bit empty (a new map is coming, so... not an issue), desert land; mine; trade; hunt for bandits, for trade caravans; research and manufacture an assortment of products, from food, to booze, to katanas, to chain mail.There are several cities and settlements, a couple of factions, ranging from bandits to the holy nation, to cannibals, and slavers.As it is, the game is filled with half implemented features, grayed-out options, bugs and optimization issues and, basically, room for improvement.It also comes with a lot of things to do, from building a fort, to making a ton of money from trade, to beating the ever living crap out a bandit boss who wanted to threaten you and sticking him in a cage, only to then hand him in to some samurai police dude.tldrThe game is not ready, but has been being updated, and, overall, has improved since my acquisition of it. In addition, it is great fun to have such a degree of freedom in a game, and I have full confidence in the developers and their commitment to their product, which is key to an early access game.If anything, the year and a half I've had with this game taught me that regardless of the goals the devs set themselves, they seem quite capable of achieving it, should you give them time."
