76561198025434087,Recommended,233860,34538919,Posted: 27 August,all,robertdrake910,"Let me start off by saying that Kenshi is far from perfect.  For one thing, it is quite buggy.  Pathing is frequently a problem, particularly when player-placed buildings enter the equation.  Crashes will plague all but the most modern systems, as Kenshi guzzles resources at an alarming rate.  Load times are as frequent as the need to change between different groups of your people, which will be very frequent for any player who builds a town (one of the main draws of the game).  As such attempting to play this game without an SSD will result in quite a lot of waiting.  On top of all this, I find that Kenshi has far less replay value than most other open-world sandbox games I've played.  Once you've done it, you've done it... it won't be significantly different when you play again.Despite all this, Kenshi has provided me with over 100 hours of entertainment.  Exploring the world and very gradually building the strength of your team, your town, and your tech is very satisfying.  There are a number of unique biomes to discover, which came as quite a surprise to me.  I was expecting mostly arid badlands considering the post-apocalyptic setting.  There was certainly plenty of that, but in addition there were a number of fantastic things to find.  One example?  A lake of solid steel, seemingly formed after a giant robot battle that resulted in quite a lot of melting of the opposition.Of course there are also precious artifacts to find in the most remote and dangerous locations.  For those who build towns, Ancient Science books will allow you to develop new technologies that will benefit you in many useful ways.  For those who don't, powerful weapons and equipment are waiting to be found as well.I would recommend this game to any player who likes to explore and gradually build their power.  That, and has a powerful modern system to deal with Kenshi's sloppy resource usage plus frequent loading bars.  If you can play it, it's actually a very nice game."
