,Recommended,233860,12194152,"Posted: 22 September, 2014",all,Easelm,"Great game in my mind. I played this when I first saw it a year or so ago, received a bit over 20 hours played and stopped until they had more content put into it. After recently coming back, it is just amazing in its current state. Given there's a few issues, it still amazes me that they are working very hard.Kenshi allows you to create what you call a ""faction"" or for short a ""clan"" some people might say. Recruit men, turn them into fighters, brewers, cookers, farmers, laborers, medics or just about anything you want them to be. Travel, build your base, research tech and grow as a community. Endless possibilities.Given it is RTS like (overhead camera, click to move a unit, etc), each member of your faction has stats. These stats determine how good they are in certain fields of expertise. You have engineering, science, athletics and many, many more to pick from. It is very important to keep a certain amount of your members to have high skill points in more than one skill, that way you can switch them when needed without waiting a long time for them to finish a certain task.I'd recommend this game if you're looking for a strategic RPG with a lot to do."
