,Recommended,233860,9003046,"Posted: 6 February, 2014",all,Chocolate Thottie,"I'm very much on the fence about whether to recommend this game or not. But I feel I'd recommend it albeit cautiously.The game is very Alpha state and for the price of 20$ it's not worth it right now so don't get it full price. However, it is getting updated regularly so once you exhaust what the game has to offer within about 20 hours you can come back a few months later and it'll be a different game.This is how your first moments of Kenshi go before you get the hang of it (about the first 6 hours for me):You will die, and you will die a lot. Enemy bandit groups will wreck you so hard kid. You will start a small settlement with a few hired hands. You will all be slaughtered by bandits/ninjas. You will begin to build buildings and move up the tech tree. You will get killed and may suffer some perma death on some of your buddies because surprise you got raided again. BUT THIS TIME you took more of the enemies out than before and from this point you can put everyone on high alert and kill bandits as they come in and you'll level up your guys enough.It's a needlessly frustrating beginning honestly. However, once you get the hang of the game there is an immense sense of satisfaction that you have conquered something and gotten to learn the nuances of a deep, rich, and rewarding game and it will have you begging for there to be more once you have reached the essential endgame of building a successful player town.If you get this, read the community guides completely. Don't go into this game blind. And pick the option that gives you 6 other AI for free and building materials for your first playthru. Later you can try a game as the cripple mofo to make your balls feel big.tl;dr: You will die a lot but if you have the patience it's worth it and this game will probably be better as time goes on. Lots of promise. Pick it up on sale in its current state"
