76561198028391188,Recommended,233860,17224153,"Posted: 25 July, 2015",all,deltabravo219,"One of my favorite Steam games so far.  The recent updates seem to have made starting a new game a bit more difficult, as instead of my character simply getting the crap beat out of him/her for the first few encounters and waiting for them to recover in a coma, they simply bleed to death.  I've also had recent issues constructing a base in newer games, no matter how far from an established town/outpost I choose to construct my base, it is still 'too close to a town'.That said, this is one of the most enjoyable and challenging games in my library.  Character customization is extensive, and there are many weapon styles to pick from.  As of this review, the various factions don't influence much of the gameplay, aside from the bandit groups, the exception being the slavers.  After stumbling into their outpost looking for a place to offload some weapons my blacksmith had manufactured, my two characters were quickly incapacitated, healed, and dragged off to work in the mines deeper in the slaver compound.  As these were my two strongest fighters, I had to reload a previous save.After 44 hours, I have a decent base and a means to generate income.  It also keeps most of the bandit hordes at bay and serves as a means to explore the rest of the game world.  Recruits in the outlying towns are providing replacement laborers for my more experienced fighters, and I am slowly building an expeditionary fighting force to attempt to conquer a town.  It's been an enjoyable experience, and the only complaint I have thus far is that there isn't a great deal of direction, which may be frustrating for more casual players.  Those who enjoy learning harsh lessons through trial and error will be richly rewarded.I would recommend starting a game with more than one character in your party, otherwise be prepared to dodge bandit groups and shuffle between cities trading goods for profit until you can afford to buy the building materials you need to construct a base.  A larger party allows you to stand a chance in combat and salvage equipment from your fallen foes, which is a quicker way to earn the required cash and initially outfit yourself with better gear.I look forward to the finished product."
