,Recommended,233860,17198889,"Posted: 23 July, 2015",all,Dyne,"I hold no illusions that Kenshi will ever be completed; as such it's really hard to recommend someone spend $20 on something unfinished. It was a highly ambitious concept that didn't attract enough support early on and doesn't have a team large enough to implement.HOWEVER if you do want to spend the money, it's still a fun experience as-is. The incomplete parts do get frustrating but if you are in it just to check out an early concept for a city building RPG, you'll enjoy yourself. It's a bit like Mount & Blade with more focus on building and trading (although Mount & Blade's combat system totally decimates Kenshi's). I don't see myself investing a ton of time into it as once you get a city going there's really no reason to continue playing, but I've enjoyed myself.PROS- Unique blend of RPG and Builder that hasn't been done in this manner before.- Large amount of research and construction to undertake which will keep you in the game for a while.- Party system works well enough, hopefully there will be more options in the future.CONS- High learning curve if you aren't willing to read the forums. Lots of players complain that they never got anywhere or that it was too hard simply because they don't understand what they're supposed to be doing.- Cities are filled with empty buildings and NPC's that have no purpose whatsoever. It breaks immersion pretty quickly.- Camera controls are atrocious."
