76561197989521605,Recommended,233860,15766167,"Posted: 9 May, 2015",all,Hellkyte,"This is the first review I've ever written for a game.   Maybe my last.  Who knows.  But I think it really deserves it.  Unique is a really hard word to put on a game these days.   Everything seems to fall into one genre or another.  And maybe this one does as well.  It's got some open world, building stuff.  It's got a sort of building a team thing like an x-com (but realtime).  It's a post apocalyptic setting.   But...those descriptors really don't even begin to describe it.  It's not really like anything I've ever played.   The setting alone is simply fantastic.  I mean Samurai Steampunk.  Why is this not a thing?  I guess Samurai 7 sort of fell into that category, but this is mort the post apocalyptic version of that.I sunk an exceptional amount of time into this game.    Don't get me wrong.  It's rough.  Like, really.  It's got a slow pace of development.  But it's also something you just don't see that much anymore, it's really a unique game from someone with a unique vision.   Watching my little dudes with their swords swinging taking something down is just so fascinating.  Watching them carry their wounded back, or limp across the desert with their broken arms.   It's just a beautiful thing."
