,Recommended,233860,15690459,"Posted: 4 May, 2015",all,Deakn,"Having been with Kenshi since it's first apperance sometime in 2012, I've seen the game change.This is my first review of any game but for me Kenshi is a great game and with whats to come I'm excited so I wanted to give a piece of my mind on Kenshi, where it is now and what's to look out for in the future.Bear in mind I play using the experimental build, you'll have to activate this on steam in the ""BETA"" tab when in the games properties.Kenshi now.....As the game stands today you can build up and entire town, make walls and defences (crossbow & harpoon guns). You can farm wheat and hemp, make rum, bread, fabrics, steel, chainmail, armor plates, medkits, splint kits, a good selection of clothes and armor and a fair round of weapons.You can manage your men and women into squads and each of your characters that you control has his/her own stats that can be leveled up through doing all sorts of things. Doing combat improves combat skills and getting beaten and hurt in combat improves your characters defense skills making them tougher.Researching unlocks more stuff todo and there are some things you'd need to buy the blueprint first and then you'll be bale to research it and then build/craft it.There is much to do but as some others has mentioned, some of these features lack depth and content, true.But having been following the game since the developer Lo-Fi, was a 1 man studio to what it is now, I'm confident we'll be seeing more things to come.So what is lacking....The reputation system still needs some work, so far I've only been able to decrease my standing with the other NPC factions (bear in mind I might actually not know how to improve it) but simply keeping to fighting bandits and sand ninjas will keep your range of towns/cities you can visit wide open.Crafting can be fleshed out more and I've heard and read that there is more to come so I'm not too worried.The world gets quite small after you've played a good few days solid but again, I've heard a new world is on its way.Wildlife is a big challenge early on and even with a small group (I've been hunted down by a pack of 8 dogs once or twice) and generally I'd like to see some variety in NPC squad sizes.Pathfinding is quite a problem now but with the ""CTRL+SHIFT+F12"" command you can usually clear that up and remembering to quicksave also saves you from the ""not too often anymore"" crash that comes with using the command or just loading in zones if you're traveling a lot.End note....All in all kenshi has come a long way and it's had it's ups and downs, but it is currently very stable and lots of fun if you can remind your self that it is still in development so don't expect a polished fully working game and there is more to come.Learn to live with hiccups :)"
