,Recommended,233860,14968463,"Posted: 19 March, 2015",all,Someasianguy,"So I wrote a review, and I feel like it deserves a new review.I like they added that you can make different squads. Like if you have a few characters that have way better combat stats than the rest of your party, you can put them in their own squad. To quickly select only them and send them to an area in your base thats being attacked. This has benefits, and negatives. A benefit is as I said above, quick selection of the group you need. Disadvantage is that each squad can only have 10 people. Once you reach 10 people, you have to make a new squad. Another disadvantage to this is that you cant have a character in more than one squad. I could put a character with great fighting ability in my combat squad, but also put him in another squad for another use I may have for him.They added a few new things, like a corpse burner. This is nice because after a while your base has corpses everywhere. And supposedly it attracts scavengers and enemies with those corpses. They also added a furnace, which will let you take weapons you no longer need and have little value. You can use these to smelt down and make iron, which can be used for making new weapons. They added specific storages for specific resources, which is useful, because once the queue is full, they just sit there until you do something. Instead, build these storages nearby and they'll automatically put the resources in these storages.I like that the shops now seem to have a close and open cycle, but there isnt any post anywhere that tells me the open hours.I think an execute action is needed, because knocking enemies out and them getting up every 2 minutes is annoying.I also had a strange occurence, a lone dust bandit that wasnt a slave walked into my outpost. One of my characters ran off to fight him. Then suddenly, my undertrained units are all fighting the slavers that were near the bandit. I never game them this command. Thankfully it didnt save recently so I was able to reload. If not, I wouldve had my whole party carried off to the slaver camp.I took down a bandit boss, who had a bounty on him, and a really nice sabre, early in the game. His body then fell through the ground and I couldnt turn him in. :/"
