76561198071309654,Recommended,233860,6645310,"Posted: 27 April, 2013",all,Hyukoroo,"Kenshi in a word is"" Rare"". Ive not had much interest in this odd themed games of post technology future esk genre but this one is by far the most enjoyable game that has been in my library. That is not to say there are not any faults with this game but rather then break the entire experience they only feel minor. I cannot recommend this enough to anyone since all the time things are being dicussed with the dev team which has grown and been very interactive with its community. Note though this game is difficult sometimes to understand and to be honest the pacing could be a bit off but that adds to the game rather then retract it. Enough of the fan writing, lets get down into a more focused view. What is Kenshi? to me it is a sandbox rpg with tactical aspectas finely blended in with management of a town you can build according to your own visions, this by far is the most fun but due to the (sometimes) brutal power of the enemy. The controls are solid if a bit complex in that you have to take time to learn which tab goes where but in most games that is a norm.The character creation is well endowed but not too overly difficult to use which can allow for some hilarious creations. Finally the combat, which is quite refreshing as you cant overly control your party or singular character and when ppl die, they stay dead which to me is a +. overall id say take this game for a spin if there is a demo and if you believe this is a game for you then id say go for it!P.S. there are creatures and not just the same human enemies, however the animals... They are terrifying :("
