76561198126890313,Not Recommended,233860,15652649,"Posted: 2 May, 2015",all,CountZakula,"UPDATE: After leaving this game alone for a long time, I've decided to re-install and see what's new, and I have no idea. See, I can't play around with it to see what's new because the game no longer runs at a playable frame-rate, and since I last played I've updated to a much more powerful PC. I don't know what did it, and frankly I don't care. If the developement cycle on this game is as slow as others have said, I don't think I'm even missing much.I get that it's an alpha, but I don't understand how the developers can be ok with selling something so weak on content, and so poorly optimized. Seriously, how poorly optimized can a game be? If I can run Dragon Age: Inquisition on max at 60fps, I should be able to run Kenshi at a framerate that's at least somewhere close to playable.Current Verdict: Do not buy this game. Seriously, unless the developers get serious about actually developing their game, I can not reccomend Kenshi to anyone. Keep in mind I am very sad to say this, because the vision the developers seem to have for the game sounds wonderful.Pre-update review: While I like the ideas behind the game and can see the potential, I just can't recommend it in its current state. Aside from following patrols to watch them kick bandit♥♥♥♥♥ or going out and getting your♥♥♥♥♥kicked by bandits, there just isn't anything to do aside from grind out your combat skills so that maybe eventually someday you just might be able to take on bandits. Yes the town building is neat, but forget having fun doing that for more than 15 minutes unless you can fight off bandits (odds are you can't). So far this whole ""be anything you want"" concept is not implemented yet. You can't ""be a trader, a thief, a rebel, a mercenary, a business owner, a doctor, a bandit... the list goes on."", you can be: A day laborer, or bandit fodder. And the world as of writting this review is sooooooooo empty and static (the opisite of what's said in the discription). I get that it's early access, I buy my fair share of early access games. But even with early access I expect at leasta fewof the features listed to be implemented, considering I paid 20 dollars for the game.As this is early access I'll be keeping an eye on developement and revisiting when it has more features. If I could give one piece of advice to the developers: Make your game fun to play! All the hardcore realistic blah blah blah doesn't mean anything if your game is boring."
