,Recommended,233860,24301226,"Posted: 13 July, 2016",all,[VD] Phallus,"I really like this game.I've been following it for a little over a year and am pleased to see how well it has progressed. Normally, I am quite hesitant to purchase early access games because I've been burned by them or have had friends lose money to greedy devs.However, this game is legit.It blends all my favorite game genres into a well crafted and fun game.There are, however, a few quirks which I hope the devs will be working on.- First is the pathfinding. At random times my toons run back to a gate to open/close it and then either freeze or go to another random area instead of the place where I am clicking. Frustrating as it defeats the purpose of having gates to begin with.- The toons randomly get stuck. Usually having another toon come and pick them up will help solve the issue, but when you're all alone, it is frustrating. Also, when I have some toons automate tasks, they get stuck under/on the stairs until I notice and have to get another toon to pick them up to unstick them.- When deleting walls, it crashes randomly. Sometimes it won't let me load the game back up so I have to use Steam's file validator to get it working again.- Every single time I exit the game it crashes. It has rarely crashed on me in game.- The camera sometimes gets stuck and I cannot move it around until switching to another toon. This happens at random times, but mostly when there are lots of crags and mountains.Overall, this game is incredibly fun and the devs seem quite passionate about it. I'd recommend it when it's on sale."
